":0}],"dname":"mjschryver","ctime_ts":1236609322,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?replyto=5629430","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5629430#t5629430","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5629430#t5629430","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5629430#t5629430","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"madcap2112","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://madcap2112.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":5629430,"talkid":21989,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5629430#t5629430","upictitle":"madcap2112: pic#0","article":"Wild Cards, wild cards, wild cards.  Don't you know you're supposed to dedicate your life to SOIAF to the exclusion of all else???  :P","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"8 years ago","ctime":"March 9 2009, 15:14:43 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Arg!","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://madcap2112.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"madcap2112","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"madcap2112","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://madcap2112.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"madcap2112","ctime_ts":1236611683,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/94351830/14903084","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?replyto=5630966","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5630966#t5630966","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5630966#t5630966","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5630966#t5630966","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"mijndraken","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://mijndraken.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":5630966,"talkid":21995,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5630966#t5630966","upictitle":"mijndraken: pic#94351830","article":"GRRM: I've only ever read Song of Ice and Fire of your books, and originally friended you to keep status on the newest books, but its great to hear about your other practices. Its comforting to know that authors that I respect and love play the same sort of games as I do. It helps me to not feel as weird and nerdy as I do around my jock dominated college. I can't imagine what it'd be like to join an RPG game-mastered by someone with such an expansive story telling ability as you do, but someday I hope I get the chance to experience something similar! I will look into Wild Cards and see what I can find, though I've noticed that some commenters are lamenting the fact that some of the books are out of print. I like collecting old books and the premise of the story seems awesome, so I look forward to adventuring.<br /><br />I'm also very greatful you have a blog, it helps aspiring writers like me get a glance into the trade and experience of a more experienced individual and get a little more perspective on what I want to do with my life.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"8 years ago","ctime":"March 10 2009, 00:38:30 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://mijndraken.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"mijndraken","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"mijndraken","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://mijndraken.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"mijndraken","ctime_ts":1236645510,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?replyto=5631990","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5631990#t5631990","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5631990#t5631990","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5631990#t5631990","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"stixccr","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://stixccr.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":5631990,"talkid":21999,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5631990#t5631990","upictitle":"stixccr: pic#0","article":"I am only familiar with your (GRRM's) Song of Ice and Fire series and with Tuf Voyaging.  I have read SoIF many times (each time through in anticipation of vol 5).  I am completely ignorant of these Wild Cards or Busted Flush works. What are they - are they comic book serials, are they anthologies, are they collections of stories about a common group of characters or times or places ... ?  References to them always seem to presume that everyone has read earlier pieces.  I would like to hear just what these works are and how best to begin reading them, i.e., with which novel or story or collection should one start and what should one expect to find.  ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"8 years ago","ctime":"March 10 2009, 11:46:37 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Wild Cards, Busted Flush, ...","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://stixccr.livejournal.com/","striked":1,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"stixccr","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"stixccr","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://stixccr.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"stixccr","ctime_ts":1236685597,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/51443191/3030116","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?replyto=5633014","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633014#t5633014","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633014#t5633014","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633014#t5633014","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"hippoiathanatoi","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":5633014,"talkid":22003,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633014#t5633014","above":5631990,"upictitle":"Elio &amp; Linda: Elio","article":"Stix, a good summary of what Wild Cards is can be found <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wild_Cards\" rel=\"nofollow\">at Wikipedia</a>.<br /><br />Alas, many of the older books are out of print. The best place to start if you don't want to dig around used bookstores is with this newest trilogy, starting with <em>Inside Straight</em>. It's made as a jumping-on point for people new to the setting who'd like to get an idea about what it's all about. If you like that one, you can start digging back by finding the first novel in the series, the exceptional <em>Wild Cards</em> which introduces Howard Waldrop's Jetboy, Roger Zelazny's Croyd Crenson, and GRRM's the Great and Powerful Turtle.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"8 years ago","ctime":"March 10 2009, 18:08:07 UTC","parent":5631990,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Wild Cards, Busted Flush, ...","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"hippoiathanatoi","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"hippoiathanatoi","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"hippoiathanatoi","ctime_ts":1236708487,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?replyto=5632758","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5632758#t5632758","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5632758#t5632758","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5632758#t5632758","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"cigarinstlouis","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://cigarinstlouis.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":5632758,"talkid":22002,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5632758#t5632758","upictitle":"cigarinstlouis: pic#85758039","article":"I first got into the anthology \"Sandkings\", next was wild cards and then SOIAF. To anyone that hasn't tried these other offerings, I heartily recommend.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"8 years ago","ctime":"March 10 2009, 16:59:12 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://cigarinstlouis.livejournal.com/","striked":1,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"cigarinstlouis","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"cigarinstlouis","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://cigarinstlouis.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"cigarinstlouis","ctime_ts":1236704352,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/51443191/3030116","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?replyto=5633270","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633270#t5633270","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633270#t5633270","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633270#t5633270","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"hippoiathanatoi","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":5633270,"talkid":22004,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633270#t5633270","upictitle":"Elio &amp; Linda: Elio","article":"Glad the signing went well. I read that Walter Jon Williams had his car totalled in an accident while he was driving to the signing, but glad to see he's okay. <br /><br />Out of curiousity, have you seen the <em>Watchmen</em> film? I'd be interested in your thoughts on it. Victor Milán's <a href=\"http://victormilan.com/blog/2009/03/05/why-watch-watchmen/\" rel=\"nofollow\">post about it</a> reminded me of the fact that <em>Wild Cards</em> was up for a Hugo against the original comic.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"8 years ago","ctime":"March 10 2009, 18:12:03 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"hippoiathanatoi","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"hippoiathanatoi","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"hippoiathanatoi","ctime_ts":1236708723,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?replyto=5633526","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633526#t5633526","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633526#t5633526","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633526#t5633526","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"az_cards_fan","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://az-cards-fan.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":5633526,"talkid":22005,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/78582.html?thread=5633526#t5633526","upictitle":"az_cards_fan: pic#0","article":"Mr. Martin,<br /><br />I came late to the party as far as the latest \"A Dance With Dragons\" discussion.  As a former angry reader who has had a change of heart, here is my take.<br /><br />When you appeared on the scene with \"A Game of Thrones,\" I personally felt that I was reading something that, while loosely derived from historical occurrences, was unlike anything I had read before.  I am sure I speak for many readers when I say that I was excited for fantasy in a way that had been missing in previous years.  When your other books appeared, the excitement mounted.  When \"A Feast For Crows\" came out, I will admit that the level of tension raised by the book was good, though not on a par with previous installments, probably because most of my favorite POVs are reserved for the Dance.  In short (too late for that, I guess), we readers are anticipating much from the Dance and are naturally excited to see it emerge.  As time has passed and there was still no Dance, I began to have those angry thoughts, wondering why you didn't set aside your \"little side projects\" and focus on this book.  I would like to tell you about a bolt from the blue, some stunning revelation that changed my mind, but truthfully, it just happened.  I was perusing your website, disappointed at the lack of an \"I'm finished!\" message, when I thought, \"Why is he not entitled to a life just because I love his books?  When did he become a slave to my whims?\"  Answer: you didn't.  You aren't.  We are all making this bigger than it should be (I blame the media).  Even if you never wrote another word, I love the stories that you have given us (ok, I paid for them, but still).  I will eagerly devour Dance when it appears, but in the meantime, please do not be dragged down by the naysayers.  Being in sales, I know how a bad vibe can hurt performance of one's job, and I imagine you face that challenge as well.  This is one reader who realizes that your life is your own, and that when you are able to bring us back into the story, you will.<br /><br />Peace and prosperity to you, and let no one tell you differently.<br /><br />Sincerely,<br />Troy A. Puyear<br />Chandler, AZ<br />troy_puyear@yahoo.com","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"8 years ago","ctime":"March 10 2009, 19:07:52 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Rhythmic gyrations with scaly, mythical monsters - please read","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://az-cards-fan.livejournal.com/","striked":1,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"az_cards_fan","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"